==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nudge
<hw>Nudge</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧j)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nudged</conjf> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧jd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Nudging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Prov. G.
<ets>kn⟦uum⟧tschen</ets> to squeeze, pinch, E. <ets>Knock</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To touch gently, as with the elbow, in order to call attention or
convey intimation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nudge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nudge
<hw>Nudge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A gentle push, or jog,
as with the elbow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nudibrachiate</ent>⟦br⟧
